A [[sentient being]] who offers a [[soteriological]] solution, or [["way out"]] of [[suffering]] by directly confronting [[reality]] with [[non-violent]] [[conflict]].

while the [[Buddha]] championed the [[Middle Way]] over 2500 years ago, in the early half of the [[20th Century]], the [[Indian]] [[sage]] M. [[Gandhi]] championed [[satya]]-[[graha]] with a strong dose of [[ahimsa]] in action for the [[liberation]] of his people.